docs.abstract: Delta Air Lines cut its estimate of profit on Wednesday and said it would decide soon whether to reduce capacity in the fall.
docs.snippet: Delta Air Lines cut its estimate of profit on Wednesday and said it would decide soon whether to reduce capacity in the fall.
docs.lead_paragraph: The price of jet fuel has gone up 50 percent in the past year, and airline executives are warning that they may have to raise ticket prices and cut capacity if fuel costs continue to rise.

headline.main: As Fuel Prices Rise, Airlines Warn of Higher Fares
headline.print_headline: Airlines Warn of Higher Fares as Fuel Prices Rise

docs.abstract: Improved screening equipment, additional flights and bigger planes to accommodate all the travelers should help. And then, there are the T.S.A.’s dogs.

docs.lead_paragraph: A record 45.7 million passengers are expected to fly on domestic airlines from Dec. 20 to Jan. 6. But unlike holiday seasons past, they are unlikely to be standing in nightmarishly long lines.

headline.main: The Holiday Air Travel Forecast Calls for More People, but Better Screening

headline.main: U.S. Airlines to Offer New Gender Options for Non-Binary Passengers

docs.abstract: Gennady Podolsky used his position as a travel agent to cheat Delta Air Lines out of $1.75 million worth of loyalty points, according to an indictment.
docs.snippet: Gennady Podolsky used his position as a travel agent to cheat Delta Air Lines out of $1.75 million worth of loyalty points, according to an indictment.
docs.lead_paragraph: Where would you go if you had more than 40 million points with an airline? Hawaii 96 times? Seoul 40 times? Federal District Court in Atlanta?

headline.main: Chicago Man Fraudulently Accrued 42 Million Delta SkyBonus Points, U.S. Says
headline.print_headline: 42 Million Delta Points Earn Special Attention From U.S. Prosecutors

docs.abstract: It may be hard to imagine liking an airline enough to buy its old silverware and service carts, but at a monthly sale, lovers of Delta Air Lines snap up decommissioned items.
docs.snippet: It may be hard to imagine liking an airline enough to buy its old silverware and service carts, but at a monthly sale, lovers of Delta Air Lines snap up decommissioned items.
docs.lead_paragraph: They come in search of economy-class seats, bottles of cocktail syrup, silverware, slippers and casserole dishes bearing the distinctive triangle-like shape of the fourth letter in the Greek alphabet, the inspiration behind the logo for Delta Air Lines.

headline.main: Stocking Up at an Airline’s Garage Sale
headline.print_headline: Want a First-Class Seat? Try This Airline’s Garage Sale

docs.abstract: Airlines have been toying with boarding plans and line-jumping shortcuts since they began charging for checked bags 10 years ago. Here, the latest changes and how to make them work for you.
docs.snippet: Airlines have been toying with boarding plans and line-jumping shortcuts since they began charging for checked bags 10 years ago. Here, the latest changes and how to make them work for you.
docs.lead_paragraph: For airlines, time on the ground is money. Financially speaking, planes only earn revenue for their companies when they are in the air, ferrying paying passengers. Which is one strong incentive to speed up boarding, deplaning and turnaround time.

headline.main: Zone 1 or Group E? Making Sense of the New Boarding Rules
headline.print_headline: Now Boarding. You’ll Need a Decoder Ring.

docs.abstract: The Transportation Department also ordered the airline to make flight crews and customer service representatives attend civil rights training.
docs.snippet: The Transportation Department also ordered the airline to make flight crews and customer service representatives attend civil rights training.
docs.lead_paragraph: Delta has been fined $50,000 after the federal Transportation Department found that it discriminated against three Muslim passengers who had been cleared by the airline’s security but were barred from flights, according to a consent order.

headline.main: Delta Fined for Discriminating Against Muslim Passengers
headline.print_headline: Delta Is Fined $50,000 for Barring Three Muslim Passengers

docs.abstract: As overall performance declined again, Hawaiian, Delta and Alaska were the most punctual, while Frontier and JetBlue were laggards.
docs.snippet: As overall performance declined again, Hawaiian, Delta and Alaska were the most punctual, while Frontier and JetBlue were laggards.
docs.lead_paragraph: Forget about perks like miles, meals and movies. At their core, airlines promise a simple service — timely transportation — yet they made little progress toward improving that basic offering last year.

headline.main: Airline Flight Delays Got Worse in 2019. Here’s a Scorecard.
headline.print_headline: Missed Your Connection? Lost a Bag? Join the Crowd
